 .TP
+.B lzs \fIrecv-mode\fR:\fIrecv-hist\fR[,\fIxmit-mode\fR:\fIxmit-hist\fR]
+Request that the peer compress packets that it sends with the Stac LZS
+compressor, using the checkmode \fIrecv-mode\fR and a maximum number
+of \fIrecv-hist\fR history buffers, and agree to compress packets sent
+to the peer using the checkmode \fIxmit-mode\fR and a maximum number of
+\fIxmit-hist\fR history buffers. Values for the number of history buffers
+in either direction may be either 0 or 1, and the default is 1. Values
+for the checkmode in either direction may be 0 (None), 1 (LCB), 2 (CRC),
+3 (Sequence Number [this is the default]), and 4 (Extended Mode).
+Alternatively, a negative value for \fIrecv-mode\fR or \fIxmit-mode\fR
+disables compression in the corresponding direction. Use \fInolzs\fR
+to disable Stac LZS compression entirely.
+.TP
